<br>
Go to other class boards, and as you leave each one you'll find yourself convinced that the class from that board is the most played class <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
In actuality, I think Druids are the most played. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uaalek.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aalek</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Holy Defender</span><br>  Posts: 535<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 1:47:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16088.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do paladins rank in numbers played on EQ?</span><hr size=1> Actually I visit a lot of the class boards and with the exception of the Rogue board The Safehouse (which wins hands down), I'd say this is one of the most active.<br>
<br>
I'd agree though that Paladins are not one of the most common classes played, although now that we have had our class balance issues pretty much all addressed, there is certainly a revival in the class.  Many many people I know have started Paladin alts, one prior guildmate deleted and recreated his warrior main as a Paladin, and I hear a fair amount of &quot;wow, I didn't know Paladins could do that&quot;.  The uber guilds that used to list level 61 as the requirement for Paladins to join have opened their doors to them.  Times have changed.<br>
<br>
I think we're definitely growing in terms of percentage of characters played, but I haven't seen any recent class breakdown that shows quantitatively how many of each class are out there. <p><BR>
<a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=131249>Duke Aalek</a>
