<br>
Yep, I still get &quot;I didn't know Paladins could rez!&quot; from my guild heh. I also get things like &quot;Wow, you hold aggro so much better than the warrior we just invited who has SoD+Skybreaker!&quot; from Rogues. &quot;You have HOW many HP??? /boggle&quot;<br>
<br>
We're doing better than we were just after Kunark, that's for sure <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
I don't think even all that we get justifies an xp penalty, however. It just makes it that much harder to get the groups and levels we need to get to our peak effectiveness... (and to be honest, I don't see much good for Paladins til 55+) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ubalidin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Balidin</A> at: 7/24/02 4:31:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=logansan>Logansan</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.users.bigpond.net.au/romagames/images/loganson.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Wandering Knight</span><br>  Posts: 194<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 4:44:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16088.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How do paladins rank in numbers played on EQ?</span><hr size=1> Paladins are one of the few class many people will play just because it's a &quot;Paladin&quot; regardless of what the class can do etc. I know when I first created my character in EQ I didn't even look at what each could do, just selected a Paladin.<br>
<br>
The only other classes that I can think of that would come close to this desire to play the class regardless of abilities etc are Rangers, Wizards and Rogues.<br>
<br>
I would also make a guess that any official count of classes would include a lot of Paladins where people just started a low level one for the sake of playing a &quot;Paladin&quot;.<br>
 <p><B><FONT SIZE="4" COLOR="yellow"><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=95857">Logansan</A></B></FONT></BR>
<FONT COLOR="#66FFFF">60 Crusader - Xev</FONT></BR>
<B><FONT COLOR="#FF9999">Founding Member of <A HREF="http://www.the-hand.net/">The Hand</A></FONT></B>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bpaladinsofnorrath.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amiety>Amiety</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Noble Squire</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(7/24/02 4:53:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16088.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How do paladins rank in numbers played on EQ?</span><hr size=1> In addition to the Safehouse, Monkly Business is also quite a bit more active than this board, and I think that probably reflects the fact that monks as a class are more popular than paladins. <br>
<br>
Allakhazams did 2 most popular class polls. The first was in March / April 2001, the question was &quot;The class I play as my main character is&quot;, and druids were easily the most popular choice (14% of the total), followed by warriors (10%). From there the answers range down from rangers (9%) to bards (4%), with paladins in about the middle  (7%).<br>
<br>
The second poll was done in April of this year, the question was &quot;What class is the character you currently play most often&quot;, and wizards (wizards??), druids and bards were nearly tied for 1st place (14%, 13% and 13% respectively). After that the responses ranged down from warrior (7%) to beatlord (2%, though almost a brand new class when the poll was done), with paladins again being in about the middle  (5%).<br>
<br>
Neither poll is scientific of course, and the more recent one had far fewer responses than the earlier one.<br>
<br>
Although paladins are no longer semi-gimped I personally doubt they are ever going to rival the popularity of warriors, rangers or monks because they will never shine as damage dealers, and in general players who are attracted to melee classes expect and want to dish out a lot of damage. It gives them a feeling of empowerment. The more subtle and refined virtues of the paladin are lost on them, which is just as well. Once power gamers latch onto a class its RP appeal never recovers. That has already happened with monks and I'd hate to see it happen to paladins. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showPrevMessage?topicID=16088.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showNextMessage?topicID=16088.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16088.topic&index=8><img src=http://eq1.castersrealm.com/pon/images/reply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.emailToFriend?topicID=16088.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.threadControl?topicID=16088.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=16088.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fpaladinsofnorrathgeneral.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=16088.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Cl